<p>I have also lived in both Cambridge (Porter Sq&#8230; Harvard Sq was too loud ;) and the Bay Area. I find that there are certainly pros and cons:</p>

<p>Boston:</p>

<p>I liked the history, and the ability to get to places like Maine in an hour&#8230;. and NYC in 3+. I liked the crazy road system as I am from London so I felt at home. I liked the people. I did find it a pain in the arse to do simple things though, and the winter&#8230;. ergh.</p>

<p>SF:</p>

<p>It feels more like a town than a city. You have to find your niche within. It has taken me awhile to get into it. Being around so much tech can start to be a drain. Sometimes I long for the time when I was living in Madison and noone had a clue what I did ;)</p>

<p>And the end of this all, I long for Boulder ;)</p>

<p>Here&#8217;s to you finding your dream location.</p>

